					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">why would the coordinate system be fractional?</div><br />It's only for physics calculations. Pretty much every game of this era uses Euler integration (position := position + velocity; velocity := velocity + acceleration). If position was an integer, you would get no change at all unless velocity &gt;= 1, resulting in really clunky (imprecise) movement.</div>

					
